icianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Looking for Some Insight into Levels 44 to 49</span><hr size=1> Fenobleu just made it to 44 and I was looking for some insights from the community about Mage life between 44 and 49.  Here are my first impressions:<br>
<br>
1) Targetable Mod Rod - costs 200 mana and when activated produces 150 mana in exchange for a 225 point reduction in health.  It now has a five minute reuse timer.  Because of the reuse timer targetable mod rod now has mostly situational utility (e.g., emergency mana battery). <br>
<br>
2) Elemental Maelastorm - an evoc based DoT spell that is comparable to Shock of Swords in terms of base damage but spreads it out over time to reduce aggro.  A big drawback to this spell in my opinion (apart from the fact that Fenobleu specialized in conj) is that it does not benefit from the improved DD damage focus effect from our summoned bracer making it 20% less efficient than SoS in practice.  Back of the book? <br>
<br>
3) Pets - I loved the improvement I saw with the level 39 pets and it looks like more of the same at 44.  My favorite solo pet is focused Torchy because of his spiffy DS.  Focused Drippy and Cloudy don't seem to be much better than Torchy at damage mitigation/absorption in my experience.   Chaincasting Muddy and throwing a DS on him seems the most mana efficient way to beat down the tougher mobs.  For grouping, I guess I will sill stick with Cloudy for the stuns, but frankly he seems pretty fickle about casting them.<br>
<br>
4) Shock of Swords - Awesome DD especially with enhanced damage from summoned bracelet.  Biggest change I see in play style is having to manage the aggro from this bomb.<br>
<br>
5) Refresh Summoning, Phantom Plate, Arch Shielding Malisement - nice upgrades but nothing so significant that I would anticipate any real changes to my play style.  On the other hand, refresh summoning when combined with renew summoning is a pretty awesome healing combination and perhaps should have some impact on the way I play?<br>
<br>
6) Canni-pet - My understanding is that even with conjuration specialization and Enshrouded Veil that using pets for mana regen is not a viable technique until level 49.<br>
<br>
Any and all advice on the Mage game between 44 and 49 is appreciated.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
