 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 428<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 8:22:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for Some Insight into Levels 44 to 49</span><hr size=1> 1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Modulating Rod</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> has never been a viable form of mana regen for mages. That honor goes to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rod of Mystical Transvergence.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
2) I had a lot of fun using them in places like Skyfire (where mobs are highly Fire Resistant), until I hit 57 and got <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shock of Steel</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
3) Agreed, 48 will be the hardest level you ever play. But when you finally get to try out your level 49 pets and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Lava Bolt</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, your jaw will drop to the floor...guaranteed (oh how I miss Double-Bolts)<br>
<br>
4) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Shock of Swords</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> will also be your best magic-based DD until level 57. It's a long wait though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5) I never got to play around with <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Refresh Summoning</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. I would have KILLED for a spell like that back in my mid 40s! You won't really notice the true benefit of HP/regen buffs until you start to use <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rod of Mystical Transvergence</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for mana regen at 56. It's nice to have though, and it's a unique ability among INT casters.<br>
<br>
6) Canni-pet is not viable until 49 and 50. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Greater Conjuration: Earth</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Monster Summoning II</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are the spells to use. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fashionmagician>FashionMagician</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:23:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for Some Insight into Levels 44 to 49</span><hr size=1> Elemental Maelastorm is GOD... I am 52 and still cast it when I solo on half of the creatures I kill.  When I am attacking a particularly tough or damaging creature.. I always use Elemental Maelastorm right out of the gate.  Low agro means I can cast a higher level nuke faster and not risc gaining too much agro.  And when that nuke hits.. Elemental Maelastorm is STILL doing damage.  It cuts down fight time, which means pet finishes quicker, which means less down time / heals you have to endure.<br>
<br>
Pet Cana doesnt work all that great (even twinked) until 50.  At that golden level you get Summon Monster 2.  Earth pet reclaim mana gain is around 4% per cast.  Monster 2 reclaim mana gain is between 7% and 8%.  Yes, this is where you will thank your lucky stars that you specialized in Conjuration.<br>
<br>
Hunting, high 40's, Scarlet desert is THE place.  I solo'd from about 45 to 49 in about a week there.<br>
<br>
Enjoy =)<br>
<br>
 <p><B>Zress</B> <BR>
<B>Fashion Magician</B> <BR> <I> <B>"((POOF!)) Your in style!"</I> </B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 588<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:46:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for Some Insight into Levels 44 to 49</span><hr size=1> I agree, the DoT line is fantastic while soloing, and I have used both heavily, even while pulling on lower resist mobs. Pull with a Dot, see how the pet holds up while you med a bit, then either nuke or heal as you'd prefer to play.<br>
<br>
Since the original poster has a preference towards the firepet, the low aggro from DoT spells is a great plus.<br>
<br>
44-49 went by very quickly, as soon as I got the 44 fire pet I jogged over to the glacier yeti cave in DL due east of the combine tunnel. Great xp, and usually enough mana to run outside and solo more blues.<br>
<br>
49 will be one of the fastest levels you go through in the game, enjoy it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The newer pet heal isn't really mana efficient for fighting singles, but if it had been out a few months ago, I would have used it instead of the level 20. If you happen get adds with a fire pet (or any other pet with a decent DS buff), I'd wager its real nice to have 2 heals to cycle. <br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Conjurer of the 55th Season-Stormhammer<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 751<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 4:05:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for Some Insight into Levels 44 to 49</span><hr size=1> 44-49 was definitely kind of a blur for me.  I remember doing it, but it wasn't for very long.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chulok@themagicianstower>Chulok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 5:54:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   In 48 hell right now...</span><hr size=1> Heh, and ya the pets are making things kinda slow for me. But, its always like that before you get your new pets. <br>
<br>
As for the dots, I ALWAYS use it. I pull with malise, bring back to pet, then hit the mob with the dot. That way, if my pet is in need of a heal, I can do that, with out mising out on damage being done by the pet. Then I can either nuke hard or depending on how pet is doing I can sit and med while they finish it off.<br>
<br>
I love the dot in groups, I can malise, then dot, then DS whoever needs it, and then med til the need for the killing nuke heh. All the time I am medding, I am still doing damage to the mob. Either directly or by proxy heh.<br>
<br>
Some mages will tell you dont bother with the DoT. Others, like myself will tell you by all means, use it. It basically comes down to your play style. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaid2373>kaid2373</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 9:08:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://isaythere.solinus.com/swgwok_f_mb.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: In 48 hell right now...</span><hr size=1> The dot is situational but is useful if you want a decent opening shot that isn't likely to agro mob on you. The other plus is it lands well after malise and if it lands it always does max damage which is pretty decent if you have an extended affliction item.<br>
<br>
Kaid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=masterdaehn>MasterDaehn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 11:19:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=167.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: In 48 hell right now...</span><hr size=1>  Hmm, I dinged 46, 47, 48 and 49 all in one evening off bloodgills. <br>
<br>
 Focused Fire pet. Send the pet in on 2 bloodgills (remain standing while doing so or the 2nd one will come thump you) and nuke the first one after he is down about 2 bub life. He will die very shortly after that. Tag the 2nd gob with a low level nuke, heal your pet once, and pet should finish fight around 30-50% life. After tagging 2nd goblin/healing pet sit and med and you should be FM about the time pet heals up all the way and ready for two more.<br>
<br>
